entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you consider yourself an introvert

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am i am an artist i draw i paint i do tattoos i work a lot with animals i like outdoor activities biking hiking

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: people that are not fair people that are angry and people that are dishonest

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: usually i will give myself like a ten second timeout and think about it before i speak or react

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am very good at controlling my temper

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably my spouse about something to do with our financial matters

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is the best thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the unconditional love my boys have for me the everything that being a parent has made me a better person it is made me a better everything a better employee i have i think being having my children made me much better person every day

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably i have a lot i have had a very full life i would be really hard to say to narrow that down i have had so many

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am a good friend i am a true friend i am honest i am real i am dependable and i do not play games i am very i am no i am no drama

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i have

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: in february of two thousand eleven

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was attacked by a stalker and almost killed in november of two thousand nine he broke into my apartment and laid in wait for me and attacked me when i came in the door and tried to kill me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think therapy has helped me tremendously i do not think i would be able to hold a job and be responsible and be a productive member of society of society without therapy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i use the resources draw on the resources that i have learned and i reach out to other people i try not to isolate i try to use the tools that have been given to me in therapy i do not use medication anymore so it is mainly just proactive treatment where i have to do something about it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is not it is never easy it is always bad

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: tired lethargic it is hard to keep my thoughts in order it is hard just to do the basics during the day

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i can not remember

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you most proud of in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is hard to say right now i have not decided i am very proud of my children i would say that is probably it they are really good boys

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: is there anything you regret

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have too many regrets right now

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what advice would you give yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: to finish school to stay focused to not let myself get distracted to focus more on long term goals than short term goals

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my father

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what would you say are some of your best qualities

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am very honest i am very calm i do not get angry easily it takes a lot to provoke me i am reliable if i say i am gonna do something i do it and i am i am not i am basically what you see is what you get i do not i do not pull any punches with people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that usually put you in a good mood

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: anything to do with animals i love animals i always smile around animals any kind big small i like older people elderly people i like to help them and be around them i like children
